text: The following line is a bit shorter: print datetime.datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')

author: @dizzy0ny
text: You forgot to put the ichart url in the description :).  I found the following URL, while not as fast, will get you daily historical data for the life of the security(replace '[TICKER]' with the ticker (and of course you can change the start/end dates):  'http://ichart.finance.yahoo.com/table.csv?s=[TICKER]&a=01&b=01&c=1900'
